## 2.0.34-arm64  (macOS Apple Silicon build)
- Native Apple Silicon (arm64) macOS build — fixes repeated crashes on Apple
  Silicon Macs / recent macOS (the old Intel build ran under Rosetta 2 and
  segfaulted). See MODERNIZATION.md.
- Build via ./build-macos-arm64.sh (NW.js 0.77 arm64). Window title shows
  "· Apple Silicon".
- Fix Backup/Restore on the Configuration tab: replaced chrome.fileSystem
  (which fails under NW.js with "Invalid calling page") with NW.js-native file
  dialogs + Node fs. Backup now writes the FC config to a .txt file; Restore
  reads it back. Backup filename now includes a date/time stamp
  (kissfc-backup-YYYY-MM-DD_HHMMSS.txt).
- Fix the .hex firmware file pickers (FC, FC v2, ESC flashers) — same
  chrome.fileSystem bug; now use NW.js-native open dialogs. (The flash operation
  itself is unchanged and still needs hardware testing.)
- Remove obsolete `--disable-features=nw2` chromium-arg.
- Add ./run-macos-debug.sh to launch the build with console logging.
- Fix serial layer wedging permanently after a single failed send: chrome_serial
  send() ignored failed sends (undefined sendInfo / sendInfo.error), leaving
  `transmitting` stuck true so no further data was ever sent (port opens but the
  bootloader handshake never goes out → "won't connect"). Now logs the real error
  ("SERIAL: send failed (...)") and recovers the transmit queue.
- Fix 3D view (Data Output tab) crashing every frame with
  "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '0')": the animation loop read
  telemetry (GyroRaw/ACCRaw) before it had arrived. Now skips frames until
  telemetry is present.

